    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="219"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/470.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Zenón Torribio is reported to have landed in the Dominican Republic via Haiti
                    with a revolutionary force of Dominicans and Haitians, and to be receiving aid
                    from the Haitian authorities. A Dominican gunboat has been dispatched to Dajabón
                    with a strong force. Torribio was one of the Morales group and is the only one
                    who escaped capture or death at San Juan last spring.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
